# Tinycardo - Cursor Rules

## Internationalization (i18n) Key Convention

### Key Naming Rules

- **File-based prefixes**: All i18n keys MUST begin with the name of the file where they are used
- **One key, one file**: Never reuse a key across different files
- **Easy cleanup**: When removing a file, you can easily identify and remove all corresponding translations

### Examples

```typescript
// In file: create_deck_title.tsx
const titleKey = "create_deck_title/title"
const subtitleKey = "create_deck_title/subtitle"
const buttonKey = "create_deck_title/create_button"

// In file: deck_actions_dialog.tsx
const deleteKey = "deck_actions_dialog/delete"
const editKey = "deck_actions_dialog/edit"
const shareKey = "deck_actions_dialog/share"

// In file: session_-_cards.tsx
const nextKey = "session_-_cards/next"
const previousKey = "session_-_cards/previous"
const finishKey = "session_-_cards/finish"
```

### Benefits

- **Maintainability**: Easy to track which keys belong to which component
- **Cleanup**: Simple to remove unused translations when deleting files
- **Organization**: Clear separation of concerns in translation files
- **Debugging**: Quick identification of missing translations by file
